# Inheritance enables a new class to receive or inherit the attributes and methods of existing classes using the same implementation, which is a great form of code reuse
# The class to be inherited is Superclass or Parents and the inherited class is Subclass or Child
# A few languages like Python, and C++, allow you to inherit from more then one super class. Bringing in attributes and behaviors from multiple other classes
# Languages like Java, C#, Swift, and Ruby enforce single inheritance with classes
